The paper proposes a machine learning model for music composition, specifically in the style of the Beatles. This falls under the intersection of computer science and music, which is often categorized under cs.SD (Sound). The use of a recurrent neural network (RNN) for music generation suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the integration of music theory knowledge into the model suggests a focus on music information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SP). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.SD and cs.AI, followed by cs.SI, cs.IR, and cs.SP.
